    <div class="section">
    <h3>Total variation distance</h3>
    <p>The Total Variation Distance (TVD) of two categorical distributions is the sum of the absolute differences of their proportions, all divided by 2.</p>
    <pre class='code'>def total_variation_distance(dist1, dist2):
        &#x27;&#x27;&#x27;Computes the TVD between two categorical distributions, 
           assuming the categories appear in the same order.&#x27;&#x27;&#x27;
        return np.abs((dist1 - dist2)).sum() / 2</pre>
